{"questionId":"9071383","questionHtml":"<p>What is the percentage yield when 7 g of ethene produces 6 g of ethanol?</p>\n<p><em>M</em><sub>r</sub>(ethene) = 28 and <em>M</em><sub>r</sub>(ethanol) = 46</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>(g) + H<sub>2</sub>O(g) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub>OH(g)</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{6 \\times 7 \\times 100}}{{28 \\times 46}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>46</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{6 \\times 46 \\times 100}}{{7 \\times 28}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>46</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{6 \\times 28}}{{7 \\times 46 \\times 100}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>46</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{6 \\times 28 \\times 100}}{{7 \\times 46}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>46</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071383","referenceCode":"18M.1.sl.TZ1.4","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"What is the percentage yield when 7 g of ethene produces 6 g of ethanol? Mr(ethene) = 28 and Mr(ethanol) = 46 C2H4(g) + H2O(g) → C2H5OH(g) A. 6 × 7 × 100 28 × 46 B. 6 × 46 × 100 7 ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.3 Reacting masses and volumes","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}